        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 8:19PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 819 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
SC State Fair Grounds, or near Forest Acres, moving southeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Columbia, West Columbia, Cayce, Forest Acres, McEntire Air Base,
Dentsville, St. Andrews, South Congaree, Pine Ridge, St. Matthews,
Arcadia Lakes, Eastover, Congaree National Park, Hopkins, Horrel
Hill, Riverbanks Zoo, SC State Farmer's Market, Woodfield, Columbia
Metro Airport, and SC State Fair Grounds.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 126 near mile marker 3.
Interstate 20 in South Carolina between mile markers 69 and 77.
Interstate 26 between mile markers 112 and 127.
Interstate 77 between mile markers 0 and 18.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
